    </table>
    <section id="sect-00005">
    <title>Adverse Effects and Contraindications</title>
    <para id="para-00011">Adverse effects for topical acne medications most often involve localized skin redness, scaling, itching, and burning. These may worsen when adapalene is used concomitantly with other substances that cause irritation or dry skin. For this reason, contraindications include the use of other non-approved substances, soaps, and cleansers that cause skin irritation. Other contraindications are sun or other ultraviolent light and the use of occlusive dressings—those that do not allow air or moisture to get in or out.</para>
